      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "CUT THE CORD (1) goes very well at this course having never missed the frame including four wins and four placings. Comes off a (25.77) win last time, scoring by 5.5 lengths in a Grade 4/5 over 461m at this track. Has the ability and looks a key chance here. FIRE WATER BURN (5) has a fair record and proved too classy last time to win by a nose at Launceston in a handy 30.07 beating Rapidly. Ran one of the fastest times on the program in his latest win. Expected to measure up again. SCOOBY DANGER (2) goes very well here starting 11 times for four wins and three minors. Placed last time (30.18) at Launceston in a Grade 5, finishing third and beaten 1.5 lengths. Looks a key chance on best figures. BRADMORE (7) boasts a solid strike-rate over this trip.",
